## Component Patterns

### App Header Bar
```jsx
<div className="p-2 border-b-2 border-black bg-white flex justify-between items-center">
    <span className="font-mono text-xs font-bold uppercase">APP_NAME</span>
    // ... controls
</div>
```

### Status Text
```jsx
<span className="font-mono text-[10px] text-gray-500">STATUS TEXT</span>
```

### Table (File List)
```jsx
<table className="w-full text-left border-collapse">
    <thead className="bg-black text-white text-xs font-mono sticky top-0">
        <tr><th className="p-2">COLUMN</th></tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody className="font-mono text-xs">
        <tr className="border-b border-gray-200 hover:bg-yellow-100">
            <td className="p-2">Content</td>
        </tr>
    </tbody>
</table>
```

### Empty State
```jsx
<div className="p-4 border-2 border-dashed border-gray-300 text-center">
    <span className="font-mono text-xs text-gray-400">EMPTY STATE MESSAGE</span>
</div>
```

---

## Z-Index Layers

```
z-0         // Desktop icons
z-10-99     // Windows (dynamically assigned)
z-[99999]   // Taskbar
z-[999998]  // Overlays (CRT static)
z-[999999]  // Dog (always on top)
```

---

## Canvas Games

### Background
- Dark: #1a1a1a (SNEK)
- Light: #f0f0f0 or gray variants

### Grid Lines
- Color: #222 (subtle)
- 1px stroke

### Player/Elements
- Primary: #fff (white)
- Secondary: #888 (gray)
- Enemy: rgba(255, 0, 0, 0.5) (semi-transparent red)
- Food/Exit: #fff or #0f0

---

## Naming Conventions

### File Names
- ALL_CAPS with underscores: `VOID.TXT`, `ORACLE.EXE`
- Extensions indicate type:
  - `.EXE` - Interactive programs/games
  - `.TXT` - Text-based utilities
  - `.WAV` - Audio/music related
  - `.DAT` - Data/stored content
  - `.BIN` - System files

### Component Names
- PascalCase: `VoidApp`, `OracleApp`
- Descriptive and functional

### CSS Classes
- Tailwind utility-first
- Custom classes use kebab-case: `window-shadow`, `icon-shadow`

---

## Do's and Don'ts

### DO:
- Use monospace fonts for technical/data display
- Keep UI elements chunky and visible
- Use harsh shadows and solid borders
- Make everything feel interactive and tangible
- Use UPPERCASE for labels and titles
- Keep color minimal and meaningful

### DON'T:
- Use gradients
- Use rounded corners (except specific cases)
- Use soft shadows or blur effects
- Use decorative elements without function
- Use lowercase for UI labels
- Overuse color - black and white should dominate

---

## App-Specific Styles

### VOID.TXT
- All black background
- Text fades from white to transparent
- Glowing text effect when fresh

### ORACLE.EXE
- Dark gray/black theme
- Serif font for quotes (font-serif)
- Mystical but not cheesy

### DESTRUCTION.EXE
- Glitch effect on icon hover
- CRT static overlay during destruction
- Hue-rotate filter during chaos

### TAROT.DAT
- Purple theme (exception to monochrome)
- ASCII art cards
- Yellow text for card display

### DOG.EXE
- Brown pixel art palette
- Physics-based movement
- Playful but still brutalist

